  "text": "Valid and reliable methods are essential to assess the presence and the extent of insulin resistance, the associated risk factors and the effect of lifestyle and pharmacological interventions. Different methods to assess insulin resistance are currently available and they include fasting measurements of insulin and glucose, the OGTT, the insulin tolerance test, the hyperinsulinemic euglycemic clamp and the frequently sampled i.v. glucose tolerance test (FSIVGTT) [CITATION_1] .",
